<p>In my <code>.cshtml</code> file I have a header <code>&lt;h2 id="venueName"&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;</code> and a Kendo Map with <code>MarkerClick</code> event defined like this:</p>  <pre><code>@(Html.Kendo().Map()     .Name("map")     .Center(-25.8671083, 133.6768307)     .Zoom(4)     .Layers(layers =&gt;         {             ...         })     .Events(events =&gt; events         .MarkerClick("onMarkerClicked")     ) ) </code></pre>  <p>Here is the script for the event</p>  <pre><code>&lt;script type="text/javascript"&gt;     function onMarkerClicked(e) {         $("#venueName").text("Venue 1");     } &lt;/script&gt; </code></pre>  <p>The question is: When I click the marker, the header doesn't change to <code>Venue 1</code>. Am I wrong somewhere?</p>